    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Most commonly a set of two objects including a small wheel and a matching die or stamp that are used to set large grommets, usually into accompanying washers. These are made in varying sizes to accommodate grommets of differing sizes.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000105033/Craft Techniques in Occupational Therapy, US Army (1971)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000018191/Diagram Group and Midgley, Handtools of Arts and Crafts (1981)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Meestal een set van twee objecten, een wieltje en een bijpassende matrijs of stempel, die worden gebruikt om grote pakringen te plaatsen, meestal in de bijbehorende afdichtingsringen. Ze worden in uiteenlopende formaten gemaakt, zodat ze gebruikt kunnen worden bij pakringen van diverse formaten.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
      </Descriptive_Note>
    </Descriptive_Notes>
